  <p style="font-size: 20px; margin:1% 8% 1% 8%; text-align: center;">
    Transportation is vital to getting around the island and experiencing some of the best parts of the island, as well as getting to the island and departure. Most of our visitors arrive by air, while there are a few cruise ships that stop by Yellow Leaf Bay once per week. We have a small airport that can accommodate small jets and propeller planes.
    <br>
    The airport is in the process of expanding so that we are able to accommodate larger jets, we are expecting this expansion in the next few years. Ground travel options consist of public buses, private buses, taxis, and rental cars.
  </p>
  
